Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
all_inputs(25.10)                                            all_inputs(25.10)

Name
       all_inputs  -  Returns a collection of input or inout ports in the cur-
       rent design

Syntax
       all_inputs

       [help]

       [-clock list_of_<clocks>]

       [-no_clocks]

       [-edge_triggered]

       [-level_sensitive]

       Returns a collection of input or inout ports in the current design.

       To filter inputs, use the get_ports command to create a  collection  of
       ports  matching certain criteria. You can assign these ports to a vari-
       able or pass them using another command. You can limit the contents  of
       the collection to ports with input delay relative to a specific clock.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -clock <list_of_clocks>
              Considers  or  limits  the search to ports that have input delay
              relative to a specified list of clocks.

       -edge_triggered
              Returns a collection of input ports (specified with the  set_in-
              put_delay -clock constraint), that have edge-triggered input de-
              lay.

       -level_sensitive
              Returns  a collection of input ports (specified with the set_in-
              put_delay -level_sensitive constraint), that  have  level-sensi-
              tive input delay.

       -no_clocks
              Returns  primary  input  ports  that do not have create_clock or
              create_generated_clock constraints.

Example
              * The following command returns the names all of the input ports
                with input delay relative to an ideal_clk:

                all_inputs -clock ideal_clk

              * The following example lists all input ports in the current de-
                sign:

                all_inputs

              * The following example sets the drive value of  all  the  input
                ports on the current design to 10:

                set_drive 10.0 [all_inputs]

              * The  following  example  marks with a multicycle value of 0 to
                the all paths from inputs having level-sensitive  input  delay
                relative to PHI1 to level-sensitive registers clocked by

                CDNSCLK:

                set_multicycle_path 0 \

                      -from [all_inputs -clock CDNSCLK -level_sensitive] \

                      -to [all_registers -data_pins -clock CDNSCLK]

